      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "It makes sense that a phone call feels like an endless loop when your reality is so heavy and isolating; sometimes the most helpful thing is to just sit in that weight without trying to push it away. You don't have to believe in a \"future\" anymore, but there is still an incredible amount of love left in you that you carry for someone who is gone. If you need to do something else today, like watching a comforting show or taking a long bath, that counts as a small victory in itself.",
